@Mark Your essay reads like a true idiot's. Who do you think funds the R%D subsidies given to private corporations? Investors? Because it's taxpayer money. Since the year 2000 over 80% of vaccines developed were funded through taxpayer dollars. Leave it to our good ol' U.S. of A. to make you pay for something twice only for you to say "yeah but this is probably the best way". 

Also yes, the U.S. is number one in cancer treatment survival rates, but only those who are treated. In case you didn't know, chemo is incredibly expensive, especially with private insurance. How many people do you think can't afford the treatment though? Because it's 1/4. 25% of Americans with cancer can't afford treatment.
So if you still go by number of patients treated yes, America is at the top, but if you go by gross number of individuals with cancer that survive the U.S. ranks near the bottom (going by OECD nations). You are given nothing but crumbs by your country and you say "no no please, I don't deserve it". It's pathetic.

